<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,236,780]" box="[151,263,236,265]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis box="[151,263,236,265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,236,780]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
Until now five 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keifer" authorityYear="1944" box="[402,487,273,301]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[402,487,273,301]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Aceria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species have been recorded on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[890,982,273,302]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[890,982,273,302]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">P. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[999,1096,273,302]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="4.[151,216,854,878]" captionText="Table 1. Aceria mite species collected on Populus alba L. worldwide and their type host, alternative hosts and habitus (according to Amrine and de Lillo, unpublished database)." pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Apart 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Keifer" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[1204,1382,273,302]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parapopuli">
<emphasis box="[1204,1382,273,302]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">A. parapopuli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the descriptions of the other species appear to be not consistent with the current descriptive standard (
<bibRefCitation author="de Lillo, E. &amp; Craemer, C. &amp; Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Nuzzaci, G." pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="283 - 307" refId="ref5047" refString="de Lillo, E., Craemer, C., Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Nuzzaci, G. (2010) Recommended procedures and techniques for morphological studies of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Experimental and Applied Acarology, 51 (1 - 3): 283 - 307." type="journal article" year="2010">
de Lillo 
<emphasis box="[226,294,346,375]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). The prodorsal shield ornamentation of Iranian specimens is closer to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1329,1436,347,375]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis box="[1329,1436,347,375]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">A. varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to the drawing by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nalepa A." box="[530,717,383,412]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="525 - 540" refId="ref5551" refString="Nalepa A. (1892) Neue Arten der Gattung Phytoptus Duj. und Cecidophyes Nal. Denkschriften kaiser Akademie der Wissenschaften: Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche, Wien, 59: 525 - 540 + 4 pls." type="book chapter" year="1892">Nalepa (1892)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Boczek, J." box="[784,980,383,412]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="393 - 398" refId="ref4873" refString="Boczek, J. (1969) Studies on mites (Acarina) living on plants in Poland. XI. Bulletin of the Polish Academy of Sciences Cl. 5, 17 (6): 393 - 398." type="journal article" year="1969">Boczek (1969)</bibRefCitation>
. The main differences between the Iranian specimens and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nalepa A." box="[451,654,420,449]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="525 - 540" refId="ref5551" refString="Nalepa A. (1892) Neue Arten der Gattung Phytoptus Duj. und Cecidophyes Nal. Denkschriften kaiser Akademie der Wissenschaften: Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche, Wien, 59: 525 - 540 + 4 pls." type="book chapter" year="1892">Nalepa's (1892)</bibRefCitation>
description regards the shape of the frontal lobe (evident in the Iranian specimens and neglected in the given descriptions, but the previous authors might have not seen the lobe due to the less sharpening of the available instruments) and the length of setae 
<emphasis box="[1377,1391,495,523]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">e</emphasis>
(as long as setae 
<emphasis box="[323,339,530,559]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">d</emphasis>
in the original description but in the Iranian specimens setae 
<emphasis box="[1128,1144,530,559]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">d</emphasis>
is longer (46–60) than setae 
<emphasis box="[225,239,568,596]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">e</emphasis>
(15–17)). Iranian specimens have been found vagrants on the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1051,1145,567,596]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[1051,1145,567,596]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">P. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
leaves, while 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1332,1437,568,596]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis box="[1332,1437,568,596]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">A. varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
causes erinea on the undersurface of the leaves and bulges on the opposite side of the lamina on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tremula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">P. tremula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Boczek, J." box="[429,623,641,670]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="393 - 398" refId="ref4873" refString="Boczek, J. (1969) Studies on mites (Acarina) living on plants in Poland. XI. Bulletin of the Polish Academy of Sciences Cl. 5, 17 (6): 393 - 398." type="journal article" year="1969">Boczek (1969)</bibRefCitation>
, whereas it is related to felty silver surface on the underside of the leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[323,417,678,707]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[323,417,678,707]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">P. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[459,548,678,707]" name="Poland" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Poland</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Szulc, W." box="[565,716,678,707]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="27 - 55" refId="ref5697" refString="Szulc, W. (1966) Szpeciele (Eriophyidae) z wyzyny Lodzkiej. [Gall mites (Eriophyidae) of Lodz Upland]. Zeszyty naukowe Uniwersytetu Lodzkiego Seria II, 21: 27 - 55." type="journal article" year="1966">Szulc 1966</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, in absence of further data and with the will to be quite conservative, the Iranian specimens were redescribed as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1004,1105,715,743]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis box="[1004,1105,715,743]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">A. varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to the observed similarities with the previously described species.
</paragraph>
